# Task Memo

## Objective
Generate subjective and emotional titles (in both English and Japanese) for 15 artwork IDs specified in `list.txt`, based on their corresponding `tags` and `critique` files.

## Actions Taken
1. Explored the context and verified the requirement to generate exactly one `.en.txt` and one `.ja.txt` title file per ID in the `title/` directory.
2. Read the `tags` and `critique` files for all 15 IDs.
3. Wrote a python script `generate.py` that dynamically writes custom, hand-crafted subjective/emotional titles for each of the 15 IDs into the `title/` directory.
4. Executed `generate.py` which successfully generated 30 files in total (15 English, 15 Japanese).
5. Verified the files were correctly created and are not empty using `ls -l` and `wc -c`.
6. Updated this `.memo` file as required before publishing a pull request.

## Result
All 30 required title files were successfully created. The titles reflect the subjective, emotional, and captivating nature requested by the system instructions.
